There are a number of features associated with lower rates of recovery from a major

22
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:24,159
depressive disorder – including symptom severity, personality disorders and psychotic

23
00:01:24,159 --> 00:01:25,490
features.

24
00:01:25,490 --> 00:01:30,330
Some of the factors associated with increased risk of experiencing another episode of Major

25
00:01:30,330 --> 00:01:36,340
Depression include the severity of the preceding episode, being younger at onset, and having

26
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:39,470
experienced more prior episodes.

27
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:44,700
Thinking about Persistent Depressive Disorder, if a person experiencing this illness develops

28
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:49,920
symptoms that meet criteria for a major depressive episode, what will typically happen is that

29
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:54,501
the symptoms will return to a lower level – such that the criteria for persistent

30
00:01:54,501 --> 00:01:59,799
depressive disorder but not major depressive disorder continue to be met.

31
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:05,979
However, in terms of symptom resolution, this is more likely to occur spontaneously with

32
00:02:05,979 --> 00:02:08,421
major depression than it is with persistent depression.

